properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: Are you ready to see yourself as a Software Sculptor? @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: Software craftsmanship has helped us immensely. How can software artistry do the same? @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: Coding is complex enough to require more than one metaphor to explain it. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: Is code Art or Craft? Not to cop out, but it's [clearly] both. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: Just like art, the end goal of coding is to be personally understood. By another human, by the interpreter. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: Like when we look at art, when we look at code, we have deeply personal reactions. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: "here is a painting of a factory by Van Gogh, next to a class definition from FactoryGirl." @emilyxxie wins all the @railsconf

properties.name: Aaron Suggs
properties.text: .@_emilyxie "I constantly type git status after every little change I make." 🙋 yup! #RailsConf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: In code, as in art, everything we do comes from who we are, what we like, and how we've become ourselves. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: Making art is a whole lot like writing code: it engrosses, builds habits, forces choices. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Michael Chan
properties.text: Thanks for all the feels on my #railsconf talk. I had a great time :)

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: Programming languages at the art supply store: Ruby is acrylic paint, PHP is pen and ink. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: Yet we are hearing about code that is "pretty," code that meets our tastes, code that is beautiful. Art, not Craft? @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: "Code as craft" is valuable to us because of the values it affords: skill, collaboration, utility, learning. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: "Code as Craft" draws on the long history of mentorship and community in craft guilds. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: Metaphors are our frameworks for the how and why of what we do. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Ariel Caplan
properties.text: Questioning whether this fits the #railsconf CoC #MensBathroomConf 😐 http://t.co/ILYTKULpWd

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: The language of computing abounds with metaphor: parents, children, handshakes, garbage collection. @emilyxxie @railsconf

properties.name: Amar Shah
properties.text: A case for "Code is Art," and why it deserves to be its own separate thing. @emilyxxie @railsconf
